frus:attachment.p:
Q. Has there ever been to your knowledge before quarrelsome disputes or
                            ill-feeling between the Americans and native fishermen?—A. No, never;
                            always on the best terms.

Question. You knew that the American fish were in the Englishman’s seine;
                            why was Farrel’s seine allowed to remain?—Answer. Because he had not
                            shot it on the Sunday, but on the week-day.
